The number of confirmed cases of Covid-19 in South Africa has risen to 402. Of the cases, 207  are in Gauteng. This is according to a statement issued by health minister Zweli Mkhize  on Monday afternoon. The virus has now spread to all nine provinces, he announced. “Fellow South Africans, as of today, South Africa has 402 confirmed cases of Covid-19,” said Mkhize. “This means there has been an increase of 128 from [Sunday's] announcement,” he said. This is a developing story.